description:
AMD driver for fixing the AHCI problem resulting from Windows Update

Works for 790GX/SB750 and Windows 7, possibly other configurations, too.
For reference on how to fix the problem check the following article:
 &lt;a href=&quot;
http://www.saltwaterc.eu/fixing-the-amd-ahci-drivers-for-sb7xx-on-windows-7.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://www.saltwaterc.eu/fixing-the-amd-ahci-drivers-for-sb7xx-on-windows-7.html&lt;/a&gt;

The problem comes when you update your AMD drivers from Windows Update (it's an optional update). After this, in many cases Windows could fail to boot. This can happen if you are using AHCI SATA mode (and you should be using it, of course). One solution is simply to switch to IDE SATA mode, but this makes your SSD or HDD slower. The other solution is to remove the AMD driver, which is a complicated proces... Check the linked article.
